13.71	1970s_energy_crisis	1970s energy crisis	The 1970s energy crisis was a period in which the major industrial countries of the world, particularly the United States, faced substantial shortages, both perceived and real, of petroleum. The two worst crises of this period were the 1973 oil crisis, caused by the Arab Oil Embargo of OAPEC, and the 1979 energy crisis, caused by the Iranian Revolution.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Nominalrealoilprices1968-2006.png/220px-Nominalrealoilprices1968-2006.png
